\f2\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb3 Key points:
\f1\b0 \cb1 \
\cb3 Building a WordPress block theme is a straightforward way to create a more flexible and customizable site.\cb1 \
\cb3 Unlike classic themes, block themes give you control over both design and layout, all through the WordPress block editor. The real appeal is the ability to customize content on the fly without touching a line of code, which feels like a natural step forward for anyone used to the traditional WordPress experience.\cb1 \
\cb3 For even smoother sailing, you can use {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.advancedcustomfields.com/"}}{\fldrslt \cb3 \ul Advanced Custom Fields (ACF\'ae)}}. ACF Blocks (a feature of PRO) lets you easily build custom blocks that fit right into your theme for more tailored designs.\cb1 \
\cb3 If you\'92re used to classic themes, you might be hesitant to try this new approach. Once you get the hang of it, though, you\'92ll see how much more intuitive and efficient block-based design can be. Let\'92s take a look.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa398\partightenfactor0

