\f2\b\fs40 \cf2 \cb3 1. Set up a local WordPress development environment\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs32 \cf2 \cb3 You\'92ll need to spin up WordPress on your device so you can build and test things without touching a live site. There are many tools you can use to accomplish this, but the best one is {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://localwp.com/"}}{\fldrslt \cb3 \ul LocalWP}}.\cb1 \
\cb3 LocalWP is 100% free, but it provides features you\'92d expect from a paid tool, including one-click cloud backups, hot-swapping between web servers and PHP versions, and powerful developer tools like shell access and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://wp-cli.org/"}}{\fldrslt \cb3 \ul WP-CLI}}. Its setup is painless, and you should be up and running in a few minutes.\cb1 \
\cb3 For code editing, we recommend using an Integrated Development Environment (IDE) rather than a basic text editor. {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://code.visualstudio.com/"}}{\fldrslt \cb3 \ul Visual Studio Code}} is also free, and it accelerates development with features such as syntax highlighting, linting, and file search.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa400\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs40 \cf2 \cb3 2. Create the theme folder and core files\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs32 \cf2 \cb3 Now you\'92ll add the basic files WordPress needs to recognize your theme:\cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl0\cf2 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	1	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
In 
\f3\i wp-content/themes/
\f1\i0 , create a new folder, e.g., 
\f3\i my-block-theme
\f1\i0 .\cb1 \
\ls1\ilvl0\cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	2	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Inside it, create your 
\f3\i style.css
\f1\i0 , and add the following theme details to the top of the file:\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f4\fs20\fsmilli10240 \cf6 \cb7 /*\
Theme Name: My Block Theme\
Version: 1.0\
*/
\fs25\fsmilli12800 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl0
\f1\fs32 \cf2 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	3	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Create a 
\f3\i theme.json 
\f1\i0 file and add the following structure:\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f4\fs20\fsmilli10240 \cf6 \cb7 \{\
  "version": 2,\
  "settings": \{\},\
  "styles": \{\},\
  "customTemplates": [],\
  "templateParts": []\
\}
\fs25\fsmilli12800 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls3\ilvl0
\f1\fs32 \cf2 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	4	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Go to 
\f3\i Appearance > Themes
\f1\i0  in your WordPress admin to activate the theme.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
