Test all pages, templates, and custom blocks in the live environment to ensure they function as expected.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 To distribute the theme for free, submit it to the WordPress Theme Directory. For commercial themes, use marketplaces like {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://themeforest.net/"}}{\fldrslt \cb3 \ul ThemeForest}} or sell it directly via your own site.\cb1 \
\cb3 However you choose to distribute the theme, you should always include a 
\f3\i screenshot.png, readme.txt
\f1\i0 , and license info in your theme folder. Version your theme using {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://git-scm.com/"}}{\fldrslt \cb3 \ul Git}}, bump the version number in 
\f3\i style.css
\f1\i0  before each release, and document any required plugins or settings.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa398\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs48 \cf2 \cb3 Best practices for building WordPress block themes\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs32 \cf2 \cb3 If everything went according to plan earlier, you\'92ve got a working block theme, but here\'92s how to get rid of any lingering jank:\cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls10\ilvl0
\f2\b \cf2 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Structure your theme with a clear block-based architecture
\f1\b0  to separate template parts, block styles, and block variations for better {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.advancedcustomfields.com/blog/wordpress-scaling/"}}{\fldrslt \ul site scalability}}. Well-named directories, such as 
\f3\i template-parts, blocks
\f1\i0 , and 
\f3\i assets
\f1\i0 , ensure a logical separation of concerns and ease future development.\cb1 \
\ls10\ilvl0
\f2\b \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Extend blocks using custom variations
\f1\b0  in 
\f3\i theme.json
\f1\i0  to provide a consistent design system while enabling content creators to use pre-defined styles without manually applying CSS classes.\cb1 \
\ls10\ilvl0
\f2\b \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Avoid overloading 
\f5\i functions.php
\f1\i0\b0  by moving any complex logic into separate files or custom plugins instead.\cb1 \
\ls10\ilvl0
\f2\b \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Minimize inline styles and scripts
\f1\b0  by relying on external stylesheets and scripts wherever possible. This ensures that the browser can cache assets effectively, improving performance, and keeps your markup maintainable.\cb1 \
\ls10\ilvl0
\f2\b \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Use the Block Editor\'92s built-in hooks
\f1\b0 , like 
\f4\fs25\fsmilli12800 \cb8 enqueue_block_assets
\f1\fs32 \cb3 , 
\f4\fs25\fsmilli12800 \cb8 enqueue_block_editor_assets
\f1\fs32 \cb3 , and 
\f4\fs25\fsmilli12800 \cb8 block_type_metadata
\f1\fs32 \cb3 , to inject styles and scripts only when necessary. This ensures better performance by limiting resource loading to relevant areas of the editor or frontend.\cb1 \
\ls10\ilvl0
\f2\b \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Optimize block rendering for performance
\f1\b0  by minimizing unnecessary HTML output and ensuring that expensive queries or operations are executed conditionally or deferred. Additionally, cache the 
\f4\fs25\fsmilli12800 \cb8 render_callback
\f1\fs32 \cb3  output for dynamic blocks to avoid repeated, costly operations on each page load.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa398\partightenfactor0

